19:52.322 --> 19:56.949
It says, Lord, that you will buy your strength, you will lead the people that you have redeemed.

19:57.470 --> 19:59.413
Buy your strength, you will guide them.

20:00.415 --> 20:04.842
Because in your, he says in your faithful love, this is a covenant love.

20:05.262 --> 20:07.265
This is a love that does not go away.

20:07.325 --> 20:11.873
This is a promised love that it finds its fulfillment in what God does.

20:13.675 --> 20:15.378
And as you look, as you read this,

20:15.810 --> 20:20.256
The Israelites, they say, this is the God of our ancestors, the God of my ancestors.

20:20.276 --> 20:21.297
They say, this is my God.

20:21.317 --> 20:26.765
They probably claim this God for themselves now because they've seen, they've seen what God has done.

20:26.805 --> 20:30.310
The God of Isaac, the God of Abraham, the God of Jacob.

20:31.191 --> 20:33.935
Now this is their God and he has been faithful.

20:34.535 --> 20:40.183
And since he has been faithful, he will continue to be faithful as he leads them now on this journey.

20:41.505 --> 20:45.330
And so for us, for us as we move forward,

20:45.986 --> 20:47.067
into this new year.

20:47.708 --> 20:51.493
As we face the unknowns, this is what we hold to.

20:52.334 --> 20:59.242
We hold to the promise that has been given to us by God, that he is our God, and that he will not leave us.

21:00.183 --> 21:04.608
The promise that he will never turn away from us, that he will never forsake us.

21:05.630 --> 21:07.992
And this is the God who has claimed us as his own.

21:08.753 --> 21:11.276
This is the God who is strong and mighty in power.

21:11.617 --> 21:12.658
Just pause for a second.

21:14.082 --> 21:16.846
How often do we limit the size of God?

21:17.086 --> 21:19.749
How often do we limit the might of God?

21:19.789 --> 21:22.092
How often do we limit what God can do?

21:22.132 --> 21:26.278
And this passage says that God, He is a warrior.

21:27.199 --> 21:29.341
His name is the Lord and He is a warrior.

21:29.662 --> 21:31.104
He is a man of war.

21:31.124 --> 21:33.507
It says, well, this is that same God.

21:34.007 --> 21:34.989
God does not change.

21:35.029 --> 21:39.154
This is a God who is still fighting for His people and for His mission.

21:40.098 --> 21:41.059
What is God's mission?

21:41.460 --> 21:44.744
Oh, God's mission is to bring renewal into the world.

21:45.364 --> 21:52.052
God's mission is to bring an end to evil, to bring an end to injustice, to bring an end to oppression.

21:53.114 --> 21:59.501
Oh, God's mission is to take His people and to lead them to the fulfillment of their journey, which is into His presence.

22:00.943 --> 22:09.874
And God has done this in Jesus Christ, and God will continue to do this and bring it into fulfillment, bring us into fulfillment into His presence.

22:10.466 --> 22:21.480
Not because of what we've done, not because we're strong enough, not because of our might, not because of our wisdom, not because we get things right, but because the Lord is mighty, but because the Lord is faithful.

22:22.161 --> 22:31.473
We know that whatever comes up in this year, that God will continue to be faithful to us because this is his character, this is his nature, this is who God is.

22:34.316 --> 22:35.137
So what is the song?

22:35.378 --> 22:38.802
What is the song that you're singing in your individual life?

22:39.522 --> 22:41.164
as we head into a new year.

22:42.546 --> 22:46.852
In middle-informed church, what is the song that we are singing as a church?

22:49.115 --> 23:06.878
God has given us a song of praise, a song of praise for who he is, a song of praise for what he's done in Jesus Christ, a song of praise for what he promises, what he guarantees to do, all for the glory of his name and for the good of his people.

23:07.479 --> 23:09.522
All God's people said, amen.

23:21.154 --> 23:24.559
What shall I return to the Lord for His goodness to me?

23:27.584 --> 23:29.987
What shall I return to the Lord for His goodness to me?

23:30.007 --> 23:35.575
This is what the yellow slip says that's somewhere on your pew back or your bench seat next to you.

23:37.919 --> 23:45.250
We are to be people of response, people that respond to God's grace, people that respond to God's action in our lives.

23:46.812 --> 23:50.898
So just to take a moment and to consider, what is your response to God?

23:51.298 --> 23:53.981
after reading his word, after hearing his word preached.

23:54.682 --> 23:57.406
What is it that God is stirring inside of you to respond?

23:59.088 --> 24:01.711
What is the song that I'm singing as I head into this year?

24:03.393 --> 24:06.477
Am I seeking strength or fulfillment in anything other than God?

24:07.518 --> 24:13.005
Am I seeking out strength in myself, strengthen the rulers of the world, strengthen the systems of the world?

24:13.586 --> 24:15.849
Am I putting my trust into the one God?

24:17.171 --> 24:19.954
Is there a situation in this new year that I need to surrender to God?

24:20.290 --> 24:21.511
who subdues our enemies.

24:22.713 --> 24:27.018
Do I need to repent of refusing to follow his lead and submitting to his will?

24:27.758 --> 24:30.001
Do I need to receive his grace in a renewed way?

24:30.962 --> 24:35.647
Take a minute or two if you want to write it down on the yellow piece of paper just to make it real.

24:36.068 --> 24:45.238
If you want to take a picture of it, just to remind you of it in your phone for the week, how is God calling you to respond to his word and to his grace?

